<DOC><DOCNO> AP880316-0078 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-16-88 0839EST</FILEID><FIRST>d a PM-BRF--GunmanKilled     03-16 0165</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Gunman Killed,0170</SECOND><HEAD>Robber Holding Hostage Killed by Police</HEAD><DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A robbery suspect holding a gun to arestaurant manager's head was shot to death at point blank range bypolice when he refused to release the man, according to officials.   Police surrounded the Kentucky Fried Chicken outlet Tuesdaynight when one of four people in the establishment was able to tripa silent alarm, said officer Dennis Norris.   The unidentified gunman died early today at Mission EmergencyHospital. Restaurant manager Waylon Gee was grazed on the head fromthe gunfire.   ``Officers had a clear shot and fired numerous times,'' Norrissaid. The gunman did not get off a shot, he said.   ``The man stayed until closing time and then held up theplace,'' Norris said.   He ordered those in the restaurant to get on the floor while hesearched for money.   Police arrived as the man was leaving and it was then that heput the gun to Gee's head.</TEXT></DOC>